  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nBesu 20.10.4, using published docker images and running on Goerli, got this exception shortly after starting:\r\n\r\n```\r\neth1_1    | 2021-01-26 14:43:10.994+00:00 | nioEventLoopGroup-3-4 | INFO  | WaitForPeersTask | Waiting for 4 peers to connect.\r\neth1_1    | 2021-01-26 14:43:15.767+00:00 | nioEventLoopGroup-3-5 | INFO  | WaitForPeersTask | Waiting for 3 peers to connect.\r\neth1_1    | 2021-01-26 14:43:23.632+00:00 | Timer-0 | ERROR | Besu | Uncaught exception in thread \"Timer-0\"\r\neth1_1    | java.io.EOFException\r\neth1_1    |     at org.xbill.DNS.NioTcpClient$ChannelState.processRead(NioTcpClient.java:180)\r\neth1_1    |     at org.xbill.DNS.NioTcpClient$ChannelState.processReadyKey(NioTcpClient.java:138)\r\neth1_1    |     at org.xbill.DNS.Client.processReadyKeys(Client.java:79)\r\neth1_1    |     at org.xbill.DNS.Client.runSelector(Client.java:62)\r\neth1_1    |     at java.base/java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source)\r\neth1_1    | 2021-01-26 14:45:47.529+00:00 | nioEventLoopGroup-3-10 | INFO  | WaitForPeersTask | Waiting for 1 peers to connect.\r\n```\r\n\r\nLike #1648 it references DNS, but the specifics of the exception are different.\r\n\r\nI have not attempted to reproduce this behavior.\r\n",
